org.logevents

Interface LogEventObserver

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    LogEventSource
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BatchingLogEventObserver, BatchThrottler, CircularBufferLogEventObserver, CompositeLogEventObserver, ConsoleLogEventObserver, DatabaseLogEventObserver, DateRollingLogEventObserver, ExpectedLogEventsRule, FileLogEventObserver, FilteredLogEventObserver, HttpPostJsonLogEventObserver, LevelThresholdConditionalObserver, LogEventBuffer, LogEventRule, MicrosoftTeamsLogEventObserver, NullLogEventObserver, SlackLogEventObserver, SmtpLogEventObserver, WebLogEventObserver

    public interface LogEventObserver
    The main interface of the Log Event framework. Implement this interface to process log events in your own way. The most used included observers are FileLogEventObserver (used for file output), ConsoleLogEventObserver (to standard out, with ANSI colors), CompositeLogEventObserver (used to call multiple observers), CircularBufferLogEventObserver (used to keep an internal buffer of log events) and BatchingLogEventObserver (used to batch up multiple events before processing).
    Author:
    Johannes Brodwall.
